### Olympic festivals in other places

*   Main article: [Ancient Greek Olympic festivals](/Ancient_Greek_Olympic_festivals)

Athletic festivals bearing the name "Olympic Games," established in emulation of the original festival at Olympia, emerged over time in various locations throughout the Greek world. Some of these are known to us only through inscriptions and coinage, while others, such as the Olympic festival at [Antioch](/Antioch), achieved considerable renown. Following the establishment of these derivative Olympic festivals, the original great Olympic festival itself was sometimes identified in inscriptions by the addition of [Pisa](/Pisa_(Greece)).

